<dl id="un3031d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un3" href="#un3031">UN3: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un3all.htm#un3031d"> (VIII.A.5) 31(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Minos</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There then I saw <mark>Minos</mark>, glorious son of Zeus, wielding a golden sceptre, giving sentence from his throne to the dead, while they sat and stood around the prince, asking his dooms through the wide-gated house of Hades. <small> Homer, <a name="OHBL" href="/udra/udex.htm#OHBL"><cite title="source">The Odyssey</cite></a>, trans. Butcher &amp; Lang (1906), 189</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
